main event: On November 8, 1967, a military pilot reported observing a fast-moving unidentified light source while on a mission, along with radar tracking of multiple unknown objects.
interesting points: The unidentified light source was observed to be reddish-orange in color,The pilot noted the objects moved within a five-mile radius at high speeds,There were no other aircraft spotted in the area at the time,Five objects were seen grouped together on the radar,The sighting lasted approximately 2 to 3 minutes and was not formally reported to higher command.
sighted object: unidentified light source and radar-tracked objects
location: 71 miles west of Omaha, Nebraska, USA
witness description: Captain Randall L. Teeuwen, the aircraft commander, who visually observed and reported the incident.
